The paper deals with reinforcement learning policies and optimization, which are core topics in machine learning. The use of Wasserstein distances and score functions suggests a focus on learning and optimization techniques, which are typically covered in the sub-categories of cs.LG and cs.AI. The application of these techniques to challenging environments and the incorporation of regularizers suggest a focus on robotics and control (cs.RO) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the mention of a demo suggests a possible focus on computer vision (cs.CV) as well.
